Detailed Description

Manages settings state for a WebView.

When a WebView is first created, it obtains a set of default settings. These default settings will be returned from any getter call. A WebSettings object obtained from WebView.getSettings() is tied to the life of the WebView. If a WebView has been destroyed, any method call on WebSettings will throw an IllegalStateException.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum gaia::webkit::WebSettings::LayoutAlgorithm

Enum for controlling the layout of html.

NORMAL means no rendering changes. SINGLE_COLUMN moves all content int32_to one column that is the width of the view. NARROW_COLUMNS makes all columns no wider than the screen if possible.

Enumerator:
LayoutAlgorithm_NORMAL 
LayoutAlgorithm_SINGLE_COLUMN 
Deprecated:
This algorithm is now obsolete.

enum gaia::webkit::WebSettings::PluginState

The plugin state effects how plugins are treated on a page.

ON means that any object will be loaded even if a plugin does not exist to handle the content. ON_DEMAND means that if there is a plugin installed that can handle the content, a placeholder is shown until the user clicks on the placeholder. Once clicked, the plugin will be enabled on the page. OFF means that all plugins will be turned off and any fallback content will be used.

Enumerator:
PluginState_ON 
PluginState_ON_DEMAND 
PluginState_OFF

enum gaia::webkit::WebSettings::ZoomDensity

Enum for specifying the WebView's desired density.
